'''''The King''''' is a 2017 American [[documentary film]] about [[Elvis Presley]] and America during his career. [[Eugene Jarecki]] directs and also co-wrote the script with [[Christopher St. John]], who produces. The film had its North American premiere at the [[2018 Sundance Film Festival]], after its international premiere at the [[2017 Cannes Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.festival-cannes.com/en/films/promised-land |publisher=[[Cannes Film Festival]]|title=Promised Land|accessdate=July 12, 2018}}</ref> It was released in the United States on June 22, 2018.

==Premise==
The film follows filmmaker [[Eugene Jarecki]] as he travels in a [[Rolls-Royce Limited|1963 Rolls Royce]] [[Rolls-Royce Silver Cloud|Silver Cloud]] once owned by Elvis Presley to various cities across America, including [[Tupelo, Mississippi|Tupelo]], [[Memphis, Tennessee|Memphis]], [[New York City]] and [[Las Vegas]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/the-king-director-eugene-jarecki-elvis-presley/|title=‘The King’ Director Eugene Jarecki on How Elvis Is Metaphor for America|first=Thom|last=Geier|date=February 5, 2018|accessdate=July 12, 2018|work=[[TheWrap]]}}</ref>

==Reception==
===Box office===
The film made $29,050 from two [[New York City]] theaters in its opening weekend, for an average of $14,525 per venue, the third-best of the weekend and one of the best of the year for documentaries.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/06/the-king-reigns-over-mixed-weekend-of-openers-wont-you-be-my-neighbor-expands-robustly-specialty-box-office-1202416456/|title=‘The King’ Reigns Over Mixed Weekend of Openers; ‘Won’t You Be My Neighbor?’ Expands Robustly: Specialty Box Office|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|publisher=[[Penske Business Media]]|date=June 24, 2018| first=Brian |last=Brooks|accessdate=June 26, 2018}}</ref>

===Critical response===
On review aggregation website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film holds an approval rating of 75% based on 77 reviews, and an average rating of 7.1/10. The website's critical consensus reads, "''The King'' pursues a wildly ambitious thesis through some fairly bumpy territory, but emerges as a provocative and insightful look at modern America."<ref>{{cite web |title=The King (2018) |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_king|work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |publisher=[[Fandango (company)|Fandango]] |accessdate=August 27, 2018}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], the film has a weighted average score of 70 out of 100, based on 27 critics, indicating "generally favorable reviews".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/movie/the-king-2018?ftag=MCD-06-10aaa1c|title=The King Reviews|work=[[Metacritic]]|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|accessdate=July 22, 2018}}</ref>

